# Escape Hatch Registry

> Copy this file to your project root as `escapes.md`. Every intentional deviation from the plugin's axioms lives here, with a justification and an expiry date. The `/strict-check` skill and `bin/css-strict.sh` gate will tell you when an entry has expired.

## How this works

The plugin's six axioms (`skills/css-layout-engine/references/axioms.md`) are enforced by `bin/css-strict.sh` and `bin/js-budget.sh`. When a violation is intentional — a third-party widget you can't strip, a legacy route awaiting migration, an editorial page that breaks the system on purpose — you register it here. The build stays green; the debt stays visible.

Every entry MUST include:

- **ID** — one of: `ESC_EDITORIAL`, `ESC_EMBED`, `ESC_DATAVIZ`, `ESC_LEGACY`, `ESC_JS_EAGER`, `ESC_JS_EXCESS`, or a project-specific `ESC_<CATEGORY>`
- **Scope** — which files, routes, or components are affected
- **Axiom violated** — which `ELA_###` and/or `ELP_###` are suspended here
- **Justification** — why the canonical CSS/JS alternative was rejected
- **Author** — @handle or owner
- **Opened** — date when the exception was registered
- **Expires** — review date. Entries without an expiry are forbidden.
- **Owner** — who reviews the entry on expiry

## Review cadence

- Quarterly review of every entry. If still justified, extend the expiry with a fresh note.
- If the justification no longer holds, remove the entry and fix the underlying violation.
- If the violation was registered under false pretenses, remove the entry and open a ticket.

---

## Template entry

```markdown
## ESC_<CATEGORY> — short label

- **Scope:** `src/components/<file>` (lines X-Y) or `/app/dashboard` route
- **Axiom violated:** ELA_005, ELP_028
- **Justification:** [one paragraph — what the CSS alternative looked like and why you rejected it]
- **Author:** @handle
- **Opened:** YYYY-MM-DD
- **Expires:** YYYY-MM-DD (next review)
- **Owner:** @team-or-person

### Entry / exit criteria (optional)

- Entry: [what made this necessary]
- Exit: [what would let us retire this exception — new CSS feature, third-party fix, migration milestone]
```

